  "text": "Our findings corroborate previous studies showing that that CS inhalation induces a robust migration of 432 inflammatory cells to the lung environment, mainly macrophage and neutrophils [41] [CITATION_1] [43] . In response to 435 differentiation of monocytes in lung tissue, amplifying the inflammatory process [44] [45] [46] . The chronic 436 inflammation of the lungs results in alterations in the parenchyma architecture, a process known as tissue 437 remodeling, due an unbalance between active MMPs and its inhibitors, TIMP [47, 48] . In concordance 438 with this notion, CS group presented, in association with pulmonary neutrophilia, alveolar enlargement as 439 well as loss of alveolar parenchyma, collagen deposition, and destruction of elastic fibers. These 440 structural alterations were accomplished by a significant increase in the mRNA expression for MMP-9",
